Definition: using the name of a part for that of the whole or the whole for the part
Example: or the special for the general or the general for the special; or the material for the thing made of it; to use `hand' for `worker' or `ten sail' for `ten ships' or `steel' for `sword' is to use a synecdochic figure of speech
Synonyms: noun, communication, synecdoche, synecdochical, using, the, name, of, a, part, for, that, whole, or, special, general, material, thing, made, it, to, use, hand, worker, ten, sail, ships, steel, sword, is, figure, speech
Category: adj.all
